The paper deals with algebraic data types and variable binding, which are topics that are typically studied in the areas of logic and programming languages. The use of monads and nominal sets also suggests a connection to category theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). 

The paper also discusses the application of classical results from universal algebra, which suggests a connection to cs.PL (Programming Languages). The use of monads and nominal sets is also relevant to cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) due to its focus on the foundations of a theory.
